div.p: Moving to London was a bit of a kick up the backside grow up sort of scenario because everybody at 18 thinks they’re grown up until you step out
into the big wide world and that was a good kick up the backside to learn different skills, to, you know, meet with different people,
socialise with different people and it made me wake up very, very quickly because if I didn’t do that I don’t think I would have lasted there 3 months, you know.
